         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Mandeville Terrace ¶ St Kilda Road ¶ Windsor […] ¶  Melbourne ¶ 21st March 1878. ¶ Dear Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M78.03.21</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">Ernest Giles to Malcolm Fraser</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Colonial Secretary's Office</seg>, SDUR/G4/325E, State Archives, Battye Library, Perth.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">This is a copy, not the orginal letter.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">check loc. cit.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Mandeville Terrace</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">St Kilda Road</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Windsor […]<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">nr = near??</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">21st March 1878.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Since I met you &amp; we spoke about Baron Muellers selection in Western Australia, the Baron tells me that […]<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">p/c is very marked.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he started to […] Perth &amp; select for himself he […]<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">several words here.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> delay any selection till he arrived &amp; it seems that if he is compelled to […] the Land that was selected for him its market value is not more than about £200 and as the Baron gave me <seg style="background-color: #ffff00; ">£8000</seg> for my Grant it would appear rather arbitrary if he is forced to abide by what seems to be a mistaken instruction. The Baron has begged me to write to you on the subject and also to His Excellency the Governor and I promised to do so as at the time you &amp; I spoke upon the subject I was not aware that the Baron had, before he started himself for Perth, Telegraphed to Mr Forrest to delay the selection. Therfore under the circumstances if His Excellency the Governor refers the matter to you I hope you will allow the Baron a fresh choice.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I am dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours faithfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ernest Giles</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Hon Malcolm Fraser</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Commr Crown Lands [&amp;c] […] General</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Western Australia</p>
         </div>
